Profile.Name: Base
Profile.Description: This is the base profile that will contain operations that all other profiles will contain. This profile is abstract.

Profile.Name: ReportOperator
Profile.Description: The Report Operator profile includes a set of privileges designed for users that need access to Reports. A role based on the Report Operators profile grants members the ability to view reports according to their configured scope.

Profile.Name: ReadOnlyOperator
Profile.Description: The Read-Only Operator profile includes a set of privileges designed for users that need read-only access to Alerts and Views. A role based on the Read-Only Operators profile grants members the ability to view Alerts, and access Views according to their configured scope.

Profile.Name: Operator
Profile.Description: The Operator profile includes a set of privileges designed for users that need access to Alerts, Views and Tasks. A role based on the Operators profile grants members the ability to interact with Alerts, execute Tasks and access Views according to their configured scope.

Profile.Name: AdvancedOperator
Profile.Description: The Advanced Operator profile includes a set of privileges designed for users that need access to limited tweaking of monitoring configuration in addition to the Operators privileges. A role based on the Advanced Operators profile grants members the ability to override the configuration of rules and monitors for specific targets or groups of targets within the configured scope.

Profile.Name: Author
Profile.Description: The Author profile includes a set of privileges designed for authoring of monitoring configuration. A role based on the Authors profile grants members the ability to create, edit and delete monitoring configuration (tasks, rules, monitors and views) within the configured scope. For convenience, Authors can also be configured to have Advanced Operator privileges scoped by group.

Profile.Name: Administrator
Profile.Description: The Administrator profile includes full privileges to Operations Manager. No scoping of the Administrator profile is supported.

Profile.Name: ReportSecurityAdministrator
Profile.Description: The Report Security Administrator profile includes a set of privileges designed to enable the integration of SQL Server Reporting Services security with Operations Manager.

Profile.Name: ApmOperator
Profile.Description: The Application Monitoring Operator profile includes a set of privileges designed for users that need access to Application Diagnostics. A user role based on the Application Monitoring Operator profile grants members the ability to see the Application Monitoring events in Application Diagnostics web console.

UserRole.Name: OperationsManagerReadOnlyOperators
UserRole.Description: The Operations Manager Read-Only Operators user role is created at setup time, is globally scoped and cannot be deleted.

UserRole.Name: OperationsManagerOperators
UserRole.Description: The Operations Manager Operators user role is created at setup time, is globally scoped and cannot be deleted.

UserRole.Name: OperationsManagerAdvancedOperators
UserRole.Description: The Operations Manager Advanced Operators user role is created at setup time, is globally scoped and cannot be deleted.

UserRole.Name: OperationsManagerAuthors
UserRole.Description: The Operations Manager Authors user role is created at setup time, is globally scoped and cannot be deleted.

UserRole.Name: OperationsManagerAdministrators
UserRole.Description: The Operations Manager Administrators user role is created at setup time and cannot be deleted. This role must contain one or more global groups.

UserRole.Name: OperationsManagerApmOperator
UserRole.Description: The Operations Manager Application Monitoring Operator user role is created at setup time, is globally scoped and cannot be deleted.
